The paper deals with revenue-maximizing combinatorial auctions, which are a topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and mechanism design (cs.EC). The paper also discusses valuation functions and item-type distributions, which are concepts in decision theory and probability theory, respectively, suggesting a connection to cs.DS and cs.IT. Additionally, the paper presents an approximate monotonicity theorem for the class of fractionally subadditive (XOS) valuation functions, which are commonly used in algorithmic mechanism design and computational social choice, indicating a possible fit with cs.AI.
